      "t_start": 48.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "The azimuthal angle phi is the relative phase between spin-up and spin-down. A different phi at the same theta means a different superposition \u2014 with different measurement outcomes for x or y spin. Relative phase is physically real and distinguishable.",
