    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "t_start": 58.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "What is the global phase? Multiplying the entire state by e-to-the-i-gamma shifts both amplitudes equally. No measurement of any observable can detect it. The Bloch sphere automatically collapses it: two states differing only in global phase map to the same point.",
