    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "t_start": 68.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "The Bloch vector provides a direct sanity check. Compute the three expectation values \u2014 sigma-x, sigma-y, sigma-z. They form a vector whose length must equal exactly one for any pure state. If you compute a state and its Bloch vector has length less than one, you made an error.",
